    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/202: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 20, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. 1. Reply is urgently desired to the Department’s 106, December 13, 5
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>2. Advise in particular, so that we hear by tomorrow forenoon if possible,
                    whether it is true that exchange is to be supplied for raw material imports only
                    and, if so, the effect on imports of wheat flour.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
